  "text": "Traced Kubernetes watch event delivery from etcd to client-go across 3 repos. (1) In sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd: watchableStore (watchable_store.go) triggers notify() on MVCC writes, sending WatchResponse to watcher channels. watchStream (watcher.go) is the concrete WatchStream implementation with Chan() returning the event channel. serverWatchStream (v3rpc/watch.go) bridges MVCC to gRPC: sendLoop() reads from watchStream.Chan() and calls gRPCStream.Send(). (2) In sg-evals/kubernetes--v1.32.0: Cacher (cacher.go) is the apiserver's in-memory cache layer. startCaching() launches reflector.ListAndWatch() against etcd. watchCache (watch_cache.go) stores events in a cyclic buffer via processEvent(), which calls eventHandler wired to Cacher.processEvent(). dispatchEvents() reads from the incoming channel and fans out to all matching cacheWatcher instances. (3) In sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0: Reflector (reflector.go) calls ListAndWatch(), then watch() -> handleWatch() -> handleAnyWatch() which reads from the watch stream and applies Add/Update/Delete operations to the local Store.",
